      • doResultTest

        private void doResultTest(Property prop,
                          Result res)
        Test a model checking result against the RESULT specifications attached to the property (test mode).
        Note: This method should only be called directly after the model checking (i.e., from run(), as it relies on the fact that the constant values in the modulesFile and reflect the values used for model checking.
        Test results are output to the log. If a test fails and testExitsOnFail is true then errorAndExit is called.
        Parameters:
        prop - the property
        res - the result

      • splitFilesAndOptions

        private static java.lang.String[] splitFilesAndOptions(java.lang.String filesOptionsString)
        Split a string of the form : into its two parts. The latter can be empty, in which case the : is optional. Instances of :\ are ignored (not treated as :) in case there is a Windows filename.
        Returns:
        the two parts as an array of two strings.
